API Gateway Setup (Connect Frontend to Lambda)
📌 Overview

To allow users to interact with the AI Agent from a browser, we need a public API endpoint.

👉 Amazon API Gateway provides this endpoint and connects:

Frontend → API Gateway → Lambda → Bedrock Agent
🪜 Step-by-Step Implementation

🔹 Step 1 — Open API Gateway
Open AWS Management Console
Search for:
API Gateway
Click API Gateway


🔹 Step 2 — Create New API
Click Create API
Select:
HTTP API

👉 (Recommended for simplicity and low cost)

Click Build


🔹 Step 3 — Configure API
Enter API name:
Chat-Integration
Click Next (skip integrations for now)
Click Next (skip routes for now)
Click Next (skip stages config)
Click Create


🔹 Step 4 — Create Route

👉 Route = endpoint path

Go to:
Develop → Routes
Click Create
Enter:
Method:
POST
Resource path:
/chat
Click Create


🔹 Step 5 — Attach Lambda Integration
Click on route:
POST /chat
Go to Integration
Click:
Attach Integration
Select:
Lambda function
Choose Lambda:
BedrockAgentChatProxy
Click Create

👉 Now route is connected to Lambda:

POST /chat → Lambda

🔹 Step 6 — Verify Deployment
Go to:
Deploy → Stages
Select:
$default
Check:
✅ Automatic deployment = Enabled
✅ Route deployed successfully


🔹 Step 7 — Get API Endpoint

You will see:

Invoke URL:
https://abc123.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com

👉 Final chatbot endpoint:

https://abc123.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/chat


🔹 Step 8 — Enable CORS (Very Important ⚠️)

👉 Required for frontend (browser requests)

Steps:
Open your API
Click CORS
Click Configure
Add:
Access-Control-Allow-Origin
*
Access-Control-Allow-Methods
POST, OPTIONS
Access-Control-Allow-Headers
*
Click Save


🔹 Step 9 — (Optional but Recommended) Test API
Using Postman / Curl
POST https://abc123.execute-api.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/chat

Body:

{
  "message": "Find chargeable resources"
}


🧠 Final Architecture Flow
User (Browser)
     ↓
S3 Frontend (Chat UI)
     ↓
API Gateway (/chat)
     ↓
Lambda (Chat Proxy)
     ↓
Bedrock Agent
     ↓
AWS Resources


✅ Result
API Gateway provides public endpoint
Lambda securely calls Bedrock
Frontend can now interact with AI Agent
